        <h2>What Is BetterHelp?</h2>
        <p>BetterHelp is one of the largest online therapy platforms in the world, connecting people with licensed therapists via video, phone, or text — entirely online. In Australia, it's become one of the most searched mental health resources, with thousands of Australians looking for accessible, affordable therapy options.</p>
        <p>If you've been wondering whether BetterHelp actually works, what it costs in Australia, and whether it's the right choice for you — this is the most honest review you'll find.</p>

        <h2>How Does BetterHelp Work in Australia?</h2>
        <p>BetterHelp works the same way in Australia as it does in the US and UK:</p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>You sign up and fill out a questionnaire</strong> about what you're looking for</li>
          <li><strong>BetterHelp matches you</strong> with a licensed Australian therapist</li>
          <li><strong>You communicate via messaging</strong> (anytime), live chat, phone calls, or video sessions</li>
          <li><strong>You can switch therapists</strong> at any time, for any reason</li>
        </ol>
        <p>There's no referral from a GP required. No waiting lists. No commute.</p>

